16/12/2003
BARCELONA, Spain -- Hristo Stoichkov, Bulgaria's soccer great, announced Monday (15 December) that that he is retiring from the game at the age of 37 to pursue a coaching career in Barcelona. On the field, his career spanned 18 years. He was the top scorer at the 1994 World Cup in the United States where Bulgaria took 4th place. He was named European Footballer of the Year in 1994 and won the European Champions' Cup with Barcelona in 1992. (AP, Reuters, AFP - 15/12/03)
